<title>USA: CLINTON WAITING FOR LEGAL ADVICE ON MICROSOFT PLAN.</title>
<headline>CLINTON WAITING FOR LEGAL ADVICE ON MICROSOFT PLAN.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-08-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>President Bill Clinton said on Wednesday he was waiting to hear from the Justice Department on whether plans by software giant Microsoft Corp to invest in Apple Computer Inc had antitrust implications.</p>
<p>&quot;We will treat them in the same way as we would anyone else and make the analysis in law that seems appropriate to the Justice Department,&quot; Clinton told a news conference. &quot;I have to wait to hear from them about whether there are any antitrust implications to this.&quot;</p>
<p>((--Washington Newsroom 202 898-8300))</p>
